                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14468360" author="roshandawrani" created="Sat, 19 Dec 2009 11:58:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s only System.out output that is directed to the output pane of groovyconsole and not System.err. Since e.printStackTrace() sends the output to System.err by default, you don&apos;t see it in the output pane.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should groovyconsole intercept even System.err output and show it in output pane?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14468408" author="roshandawrani" created="Sat, 19 Dec 2009 13:11:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching a patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14468434" author="roshandawrani" created="Sat, 19 Dec 2009 13:15:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Re-attaching the screenshot due to a typo in the code in the previous one.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14468489" author="roshandawrani" created="Mon, 28 Dec 2009 13:56:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any feedback on this patch? Safe to apply it?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14468467" author="blackdrag" created="Mon, 28 Dec 2009 18:19:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;well... I am currently asking myself why SystemOutputInterceptor cannot be used instead of duplicating the class into a new one. Also I think we maybe want that ouput in another colour or something like that. So I wonder if not instead a different callback might be needed. A different colour would surely be a feature, so maybe out of the scope for this issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Guillaume what do you think? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14468438" author="roshandawrani" created="Mon, 28 Dec 2009 21:07:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is another patch that avoids the duplicate class. I avoided it earlier as its name was SystemOutInterceptor and I didn&apos;t want to use it with that name for both out and err. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regarding different coloring for out and err, I don&apos;t think that implementation should get hindered because we have functionality to capture both out and err in one class. We can add a getter that tells whether this class is capturing out or err and coloring component can act accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14468429" author="guillaume" created="Tue, 29 Dec 2009 10:45:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Still catching up with emails &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
I haven&apos;t yet looked at the patch.&lt;br/&gt;
Just a couple comments I&apos;d like to make:&lt;br/&gt;
1) We should differentiate out and err on the output area, so that we have two different colours (normal, and red for the errors).&lt;br/&gt;
2) It should be an option to show / hide stacktraces, which should appear in the view menu.&lt;br/&gt;
Also, I think it has to play nice with the stacktrace hyperlinking (click to go to the line where the error occured).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14468468" author="roshandawrani" created="Tue, 29 Dec 2009 11:18:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Such hyperlinking, coloring, new UI options are all part of this defect JIRA?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14468531" author="guillaume" created="Tue, 29 Dec 2009 11:41:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Well, it&apos;s not because a new ticket is opened in JIRA that we need to fix / implement what is asked for.&lt;br/&gt;
Furthermore, we have to put this in perspective with what we have at hand already, so that it should play well with what we have.&lt;br/&gt;
So the ticket alone, it&apos;s indeed just about outputing err in the output area, but we should consider the whole topic.&lt;br/&gt;
And in this case, when there&apos;s an unexpected exception thrown, it&apos;s displayed in the console already, in red, with hyperlinking.&lt;br/&gt;
So I&apos;d expect to see the same behaviour when I explicitely ask printStackTrace().&lt;br/&gt;
What bothers me is that currently, when there&apos;s an exception thrown and not caught, it&apos;s output on err already, in the dos / shell window.&lt;br/&gt;
So if we always output err to the output window, we&apos;ll always see the full stacktrace instead of just the nice small sanitized one.&lt;br/&gt;
Another reason why this defect bothers me a bit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14468516" author="roshandawrani" created="Tue, 29 Dec 2009 11:48:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sounds perfect. I am sorry I tried it in my narrow-minded way.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14468439" author="guillaume" created="Tue, 29 Dec 2009 12:01:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Don&apos;t be sorry, you&apos;re not narrow-minded way at all, don&apos;t worry!!! It&apos;s probably more me being too demanding or wanting to cover all possible things at the same time!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14468488" author="roshandawrani" created="Tue, 29 Dec 2009 12:11:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am not worried at all actually. I just wanted to say something nice and then rush to a narrow-scope issue that suited me better &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14468671" author="roshandawrani" created="Thu, 7 Jan 2010 05:46:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Guillaume,&lt;br/&gt;
Back to this issue &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have now made all the changes - &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Capturing std err in output pane&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;different colors for sys.out and sys.err output&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;hyperlinking&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;new menu option for turning on/off the capturing of sys.err output in groovyconsole output pane&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Although hyperlinking style appears fine in the output - actual clicking and going to that line in the script in groovyconsole is not working for me - but it is not working even without my changes on trunk as well as on 1.7.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Was clicking on hyperlink and going to that line working? On windows?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14468567" author="roshandawrani" created="Thu, 7 Jan 2010 05:48:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I need feedback on this new set of changes. Please review all V3* files (that is the newest set of screenshots/patch files)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14468586" author="blackdrag" created="Thu, 7 Jan 2010 07:01:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That error messages from the EDT were not shown in the console made swing development quite bad, so it is a very good thing it is working now. The patch looks good to me&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14468543" author="roshandawrani" created="Thu, 7 Jan 2010 07:44:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Guillaume, is it ok if I commit the changes?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14468585" author="guillaume" created="Thu, 7 Jan 2010 16:08:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Roshan, I haven&apos;t had time to double check, but I&apos;m sure it&apos;s just perfect. You&apos;ve taken care of my various points, all is clear!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14468690" author="roshandawrani" created="Thu, 7 Jan 2010 22:06:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
